## 2026-07-15 — Session 1: Scaffold, stack, foundations

### Scaffold decisions
- **Framework: Next.js 16.2.10 (App Router, TypeScript, `src/` dir, `@/*` alias).** `create-next-app@latest`
  resolved to Next 16 + React 19.2 + Tailwind v4. Roadmap Epic 9 says "the CIA frontend is already
  Next.js (TypeScript), so this builds on that" and "latest App Router" — honored.
- **Read the bundled Next 16 docs first** (`node_modules/next/dist/docs`) per the project's own
  `AGENTS.md` warning. Key breaking changes that affect this build:
  - `params`/`searchParams` are now **Promises** — dynamic route pages must `await props.params`.
    Applied in `app/dashboards/[id]/page.tsx` (thin async server component → renders client view).
  - Turbopack is the default dev/build bundler; `next lint` is removed (script is `eslint`). Left as-is.
- **Design system: Tailwind v4 + shadcn/ui (radix-nova preset, neutral base).** Matches Epic 9's
  "Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui" line. shadcn CLI would not emit `form.tsx` (silent no-op on this
  registry/preset), so `form.tsx` was written by hand using the project's unified `radix-ui`
  import pattern (same one shadcn used for `label`/`button`). Not a deviation — same source component.
- **react-grid-layout resolved to v2.2.3, a full rewrite of the v1 API.** This matters:
  - No `WidthProvider` HOC anymore — use the `useContainerWidth()` hook (`width`, `containerRef`, `mounted`).
  - Config is grouped: `gridConfig` (cols/rowHeight/margin), `dragConfig` (enabled/handle),
    `resizeConfig` (enabled/handles). `onLayoutChange(layout)` returns `readonly LayoutItem[]`.
  - Removed the stale `@types/react-grid-layout` (v1 types) — v2 ships its own `.d.ts`.
  - The `{x,y,w,h}` `LayoutItem` shape still maps 1:1 onto RFC `Widget.position` (Epic 9 requirement).
- **Other stack (all Epic 9-specified):** Recharts 3, TanStack Query 5, react-hook-form 7 + zod 4,
  zustand 5, lucide-react, next-themes (light/dark/system), sonner, date-fns.

### Architecture decisions
- **Mock service layer isolation.** `src/services/mock/*` holds ALL mock internals (in-memory store,
  seed, network simulation, widget-result engine). Public facades `dashboard.service.ts` /
  `chart.service.ts` expose ONLY the HTTP contract shapes from the RFC. Swapping to a real
  `cia-backend` = rewrite one facade file per service to `fetch`; delete `mock/`. No UI touches mock code.
- **Server state = TanStack Query; UI state = Zustand.** Per house rules, server data never lives in
  Zustand. Zustand holds only dashboard-editor UI state (edit mode, draft grid layout, active filters).

### Component & data-flow decisions
- **Two service facades only** (`dashboard.service.ts`, `chart.service.ts`) are the entire public
  API surface; all mock internals live in `services/mock/*` (store, seed, network sim, result
  engine, pagination, ids, config). Going live = rewrite the two facades to `fetch`, delete `mock/`.
- **Widget-result state machine** lives in `mock/result-engine.ts` and drives the Epic 7 enum:
  - `chart_unavailable` — data-driven: seeded soft-deleted chart (real soft-delete path).
  - `filter_conflict`  — data-driven & filter-bar-triggerable: a chart pinned to country=MX vs a
    dashboard filtered to BR. Change the country filter live and the state appears/clears.
  - `stale` → `ok`     — time-driven via a compressed 30s freshness window + 4s revalidate window,
    so stale-while-revalidate is observable on the 20s results poll.
  - `rate_limited`     — seeded demo widget that recovers after Retry-After (12s); "Retry now" works.
  - `forbidden`        — seeded demo widget (rare in practice; seeded so the state is renderable).
  - `loading` / network-error — client-derived by TanStack Query, not wire payload.
  The "Onboarding funnel — Q2" seed dashboard surfaces ALL of these at once (6 widgets).
- **react-grid-layout v2 hook API**: `useContainerWidth()` + grouped `gridConfig`/`dragConfig`/
  `resizeConfig`. Drag is restricted to the widget header handle so chart hover/tooltip still work.
  Draft layout is held in the Zustand editor store; "Save layout" (or exiting edit mode while dirty)
  persists via the batch `updateWidgetLayout` (one round trip = Epic 3 batch-write intent).
- **Charts palette**: consulted the dataviz skill; series use its validated categorical palette
  (light + dark steps) as CSS vars in globals.css, validated with the skill's script (light-mode
  worst adjacent CVD ΔE 9.1 ≥ 8). Identity is never color-alone — legend + tooltip always present.
- **Recharts renderer** branches on `visualization_type` (line/bar/area) though V1 data is `line`,
  matching the backend's viz-type-branching intent (Epic 5) so new types need no re-architecture.
- **Global filter** is direct controlled inputs (not RHF) with zod validation only on
  `app_version_min` — RHF+zod is reserved for the Dashboard/Chart create-edit forms per Epic 9.
  Filter changes re-run the results query immediately; an owner can "Save as default" (PATCH filters).

### Deviations from Epic 9 / RFC (all minor, all justified)
1. **Compressed 30s freshness window** instead of the RFC's minute-to-hour adaptive TTLs — the real
   TTLs are invisible in a demo; server-side TTL semantics return with cia-backend. (mock/config.ts)
2. **UUID v4** (crypto.randomUUID) instead of RFC's v7 — mock sorts by explicit `updated_at`, not id
   time-ordering, so v4 suffices. (mock/ids.ts)
3. **Dashboard delete uses a confirmation dialog.** The roadmap's "no confirmation" note applies to
   *chart* soft-delete only; dashboard delete is hard + destructive, so a confirm step is warranted.
   Chart delete is one-click soft-delete with no confirm, exactly as specified.
4. **can_mutate = owner === principal** for both dashboards and charts. The RFC's `cia-analytics-admin`
   super-owner bypass for dashboards is not modeled (no admin identity in a single-user mock); the
   seam is `store.canMutate()` — add the admin check there when roles exist.
5. **Search shipped in M2** (client-side, by name/owner/tag) — Epic 9 explicitly defaults search to
   M2/M3, so this is in-scope, not scope creep.

### Explicit stubs / TODO for the real backend
- **List pagination**: the mock + hooks honor cursor/`next_cursor`/limit, but the list UIs render
  page 1 only (no infinite scroll / "load more"). Volume is low (~250 DAU); wire useInfiniteQuery
  when needed. `paginate()` already returns correct cursors.
- **Auth/identity**: `lib/session.ts` hard-codes the mock principal. Swap `getCurrentUserId()` for the
  Okta `cia-user` session when auth lands; components already read from this seam.
- **cia-analytics-admin super-owner**: not modeled (see deviation 4).
- **Single-widget refresh** (`/widgets/:wid/result`): only the batch results endpoint is consumed
  (Epic 3 primary path); per-widget "Retry now" refetches the whole batch. Fine until the single
  endpoint's ship decision is made (open in roadmap Epic 3).
- **Change-log / versioning UI**: out of Epic 9 scope (backend read-model, M1) — not built.

