## 2026-07-15 — Session 2: QA / review fixes (must-fix #1–#5 + minor findings)

Post-build review by qa-engineer + review-engineer. All must-fix items addressed; verification at end.

### Must-fix
1. **Widget chart lookup resolved by id, not by paginated list.** `dashboard-view.tsx` previously built
   `chartsById` from `useCharts()` (generic `/api/charts` list, page 1, max 20) — any widget whose chart
   sorted past page 1 was mislabeled "Unavailable chart" and lost its menu, even though the result data
   rendered fine (the engine resolves by id). Fix: new `getChartsByIds(ids)` service resolver +
   `useChartsByIds(ids)` hook (`queryKeys.charts.byIds`), keyed on the widget set. `WidgetCard` now takes
   a resolved `chartName?: string` instead of a `ChartListItem`. Independent of chart volume/sort order.
2. **"Only the two facades touch mock/" is now actually true.** Moved `ApiError` to `src/lib/api-error.ts`
   (non-mock) — imported by `lib/errors.ts`, `providers/query-provider.tsx`, and both facades; `mock/network.ts`
   imports it too. `lib/session.ts` is now standalone (owns `CURRENT_USER_ID`); `mock/config.ts` sources
   `MOCK_PRINCIPAL` FROM `lib/session` (reverse dep — deleting `mock/` can't break session). Verified by grep:
   no non-mock/non-facade file imports `services/mock`, and `MOCK_PRINCIPAL` appears only in mock + the two facades.
3. **localStorage persistence for the mock store** (previously in-memory only — created dashboards/layouts/forks
   vanished on reload, silently undercutting the canonical-URL sharing bet). `mock/store.ts` gains
   `persistStore()` / `hydrateStore()` over the durable record maps (not the ephemeral `runtime` cache);
   `mock/network.ts` splits `withNetwork` into `withRead` (latency+fail) and `withWrite` (latency+fail then
   write-through persist); every facade mutation now uses `withWrite`. `ensureSeeded` hydrates if present,
   else seeds + persists. Key `cia-dashboards.mock.v1`; corrupt/absent payload falls back to seed; SSR no-ops.
4. **Layout no longer marked dirty on widget add/remove.** `dashboard-grid.tsx` stopped dirtying on every
   `onLayoutChange` (which fires on mount/add/remove too). It now commits layout ONLY on `onDragStop` /
   `onResizeStop` (real user gestures) via a renamed `onCommitLayout` prop. `syncLayout` (see minor list)
   re-baselines the draft after add/remove without touching `layoutDirty`.
5. **Keyboard operability for the grid** (was mouse/touch-only). The widget drag handle (`widget-card.tsx`)
   now handles Arrow keys = move 1 grid unit, Shift+Arrow = resize, via `onMove`/`onResize` callbacks that
   clamp to grid bounds (`GRID_COLS`, `WIDGET_MIN_W/H`) in `dashboard-view.tsx` and mark a genuine edit. The
   resize handle is replaced with an announced, focusable `role="button"` element (`resizeConfig.handleComponent`)
   with an aria-label pointing to the Shift+Arrow path; handle gets a visible focus ring.
   Trade-off flagged: keyboard *resize* is wired through the drag handle (Shift+Arrow), not the corner
   handle itself — the corner handle is now announced/focusable but its own key events aren't bound (rgl owns it).
   This gives full keyboard move+resize parity via one focus target; deep per-handle key binding is left to rgl.

### Minor findings (all done)
- `addWidget` now rejects a soft-deleted `chart_id` (parity with `chart.service` `requireChart`).
- `syncLayout` wired: re-baselines draft on widget add/remove; changed to MERGE (keep unsaved draft positions
  for surviving widgets, seed server position for new, drop removed) and to NOT reset `layoutDirty`, so an
  add/remove never discards pending drags. Effect keyed on the widget-id set (doesn't fire on result polls).
- `AddWidgetDialog.nextPosition` now computes from the live draft `positions` (passed down through
  `DashboardEditBar`), not server-confirmed widgets — a new widget won't land on an unsaved dragged position.
- `ChartPicker` search debounced with `useDebouncedValue(search, 250)` (parity with the two list pages).
- Removed dead `"conflict"` value from `ApiErrorCode` (nothing threw/handled 409). A future backend adding
  409 is a one-line enum change.
- Two-step create-chart→add-widget flow: added a `TODO(real-backend)` comment flagging the orphan-on-partial-
  failure seam (unreachable today since `WRITE_ERROR_RATE = 0`).
- 320px overflow: dashboard header actions row changed from `shrink-0` to `flex-wrap justify-end` so buttons
  wrap instead of overflowing at narrow widths.

