## 2026-07-15 — Session 3: post-QA fixes (P1 data-integrity + P2–P4 cosmetics)

Final QA/review pass confirmed Session 2's 5 must-fix + 7 minor items all working live, zero regressions.
One real issue (P1) + three low-severity items remained.

### P1 (must fix) — keyboard grid moves could persist overlapping positions
Fix #4 intentionally unwired `onLayoutChange`, so react-grid-layout's own collision/compaction never
feeds back into the Zustand draft. The keyboard handlers clamped to grid EDGES but not to other widgets'
cells — RGL compacts visually, but "Save layout" persisted raw overlapping `{x,y,w,h}` (a real problem
for Epic 3's planned backend no-overlap validation).
- Fix: added `rectsOverlap()` + a `commitWidgetPosition()` guard in `dashboard-view.tsx`. `moveWidget`/
  `resizeWidget` compute the target rect (edge-clamped as before) then commit ONLY if it doesn't overlap
  any other widget's current draft position; otherwise the edit is rejected (position unchanged).
- **Approach: rejection, not displacement.** Rationale: rejection is simpler and *cannot* yield a
  still-overlapping persisted result (a displacement/push-down could cascade into new overlaps needing a
  full compaction pass to get right). UX matches the existing edge-clamp behavior — the widget "hits a
  wall" and stops. The check lives entirely in the keyboard commit path; `onLayoutChange` was NOT
  re-wired, so fix #4's add/remove-not-dirty behavior is preserved.

### Low-severity
- **P2** — "Unavailable chart" title no longer flashes while `useChartsByIds` is pending. `WidgetCard`
  takes `chartNamePending`; when there's no resolved name yet, the widget-result state isn't
  `chart_unavailable`, and the lookup is still pending, it renders a title Skeleton instead of the
  false-negative label. A genuinely deleted chart (result state `chart_unavailable`) still labels
  immediately.
- **P3** — `AccessibleResizeHandle` was a focusable `role="button"` with no key handler = dead-end Tab
  stop. Made it pointer-only (`aria-hidden`, out of tab order). Keyboard resize is fully covered by the
  drag handle's Shift+Arrow (whose aria-label announces it), so nothing is lost for AT users. This
  supersedes Session 2's "announce the resize handle" note — a labeled-but-inert focus stop was worse
  than delegating to the one working keyboard target.
- **P4** — added a KNOWN GAP comment to `hydrateStore()`: validation is shape-only (top-level
  `Array.isArray`), migration is just the `.v1` key suffix. Documented the "bump to .v2 / add per-record
  validate+migrate" path for future schema changes; real schema evolution belongs to cia-backend/Datomic.
- **Skipped (optional):** ~1s transient layout-scale flash at 320px on cold load before
  `useContainerWidth()`'s ResizeObserver settles. Cosmetic only and not a quick fix (inherent to the
  measure-then-mount pattern); would need a measured-before-mount gate that trades the flash for a blank
  frame. Left as-is.

### Verification (2026-07-15, session 3)
- `tsc --noEmit`: PASS · `eslint .`: PASS (0/0) · `next build` (Turbopack): PASS, all 5 routes.

