## 2026-07-15 — Session 4: Y-move compaction bug + first unit-test suite

Fourth QA pass confirmed all Session-3 fixes working, found one precisely-diagnosed bug.

### Bug — keyboard Y-moves persisted a value that never rendered
react-grid-layout v2 runs its vertical compactor on EVERY `layout` prop change, not just during a
pointer drag. The mouse path is self-consistent (RGL computes the compacted value before calling
`onDragStop`). The keyboard path computed positions OUTSIDE RGL (edge-clamp + overlap check) and fed
them via the `layout` prop — RGL silently recompacted for display while the Zustand draft (and thus
"Save layout") kept the raw, uncompacted value. Repro: on "Growth overview — LatAm", remove the bottom
widget, Tab to the top-left widget's handle, ArrowDown → `localStorage` recorded `y:0→1` but the on-screen
transform never moved. Scoped to Y (RGL's default compactor is vertical-only); X + resize unaffected.

Fix: extracted the keyboard-commit logic into a pure module `src/lib/grid-layout.ts` and reconcile the
accepted move with **RGL's own exported `verticalCompactor`** before persisting, so the draft is
byte-for-byte what RGL renders. `computeKeyboardCommit(positions, id, target, cols)`:
  1. reject (null) if `target` overlaps another widget — P1's rejection guard, unchanged;
  2. else place `target` and run `verticalCompactor.compact(layout, cols)`;
  3. if the compacted result equals the input → null (a no-op must not dirty the layout).
`dashboard-view.tsx`'s `moveWidget`/`resizeWidget` now call `clampedMove`/`clampedResize` +
`computeKeyboardCommit`. The Y-into-empty-space case now correctly collapses to a no-op (verified: the
compactor pulls the widget straight back to its original row). **`onLayoutChange` stays unwired — fix #4
is preserved** (confirmed by a store unit test, below). Chose RGL's real compactor over re-implementing
its rule, so the two can't drift.

### First unit-test suite — Vitest + React Testing Library
Stack: `vitest` (v4, oxc transform — no `@vitejs/plugin-react`, whose Babel-8 peer conflicts with the
Babel 7 shadcn pulls in), `jsdom`, `@testing-library/react` + `/dom`. Config: `vitest.config.ts`
(jsdom env, `@` alias, `src/**/*.test.{ts,tsx}`). Scripts: `npm test` (`vitest run`), `npm run test:watch`.
**37 tests / 5 files, all passing.** Coverage, prioritizing the logic that has actually broken:
- `src/lib/grid-layout.test.ts` — `rectsOverlap` (edge-touching ≠ overlap), clamps, `collidesWithOthers`
  (self-exclusion), and `computeKeyboardCommit`: accept-into-free-space, **reject-on-overlap**, and the
  **Y-into-empty-space no-op REGRESSION test** for the bug just fixed, so it can't silently return.
- `src/stores/dashboard-editor.store.test.ts` — pins **fix #4**: `setLayout` is the only dirtying action;
  `syncLayout` (the add/remove path) never touches `layoutDirty`; `syncLayout` merge semantics (survivors
  keep unsaved draft position, new widgets get server position, removed drop out).
- `src/services/mock/store.test.ts` — `persistStore`/`hydrateStore` round-trip, runtime cache not
  persisted, seed-fallback on absent/corrupt/wrong-shape payloads, SSR (`window` undefined) no-op.
- `src/services/chart.service.test.ts` — `getChartsByIds`: dedup, missing ids omitted, soft-deleted
  excluded, order-independent membership, mixed input (network mocked out for determinism).
- `src/components/dashboard/widget-result-view.test.tsx` — RTL, one test per state in the exhaustive
  switch (loading / network-error / ok / stale / chart_unavailable / filter_conflict / rate_limited /
  forbidden); Recharts stubbed via `vi.mock`.

Still untested (noted for a future pass, lower value/higher setup cost): the RGL-rendered grid wiring
itself (`onDragStop`/`onResizeStop` → dirty) — jsdom lacks layout boxes RGL needs, so this stays on
manual QA + the store-contract test above; full form flows (react-hook-form + zod); TanStack Query hooks.

