## 2026-07-16 — Session 6: mock filters now actually reshape chart numbers

**Bug (found by the user testing the Docker build):** `buildSeries()` in `result-engine.ts` only used
`filters.date_range.preset` to shape the data. `filters.platform` / `filters.app_version_min` were never
referenced; `filters.country` was only read by `hasFilterConflict()` (a binary ok↔filter_conflict flip
for one demo widget). So changing platform/country/app-version visibly changed nothing on any normal
widget — reading as "filters aren't dynamic," even though TanStack Query refetch was correctly wired
(queryKey includes `filters`); it was recomputing against inputs that didn't affect the output.

**Why 4 rounds of QA missed it:** QA exercised the `filter_conflict` binary flip (the one demo widget
pinned to a conflicting country), not whether *other* widgets' actual numbers respond to filter changes —
a narrower check than the real requirement.

**Fix** (`src/services/mock/result-engine.ts`): all four filter dimensions now influence output.
- `filterKey(filters)` — a stable, order-independent (`platform` sorted) seed fragment covering
  date_range + platform + country + app_version_min, folded into the PRNG seed → each distinct filter
  combination gets its own curve shape, not just a rescale.
- `filterScale(filters)` — a magnitude multiplier mirroring a WHERE-narrowed Pinot query returning
  *less* volume: empty platform = all (×1), each selected platform ≈ ×0.55; a single country takes its
  rough share (`COUNTRY_SHARE`, br .45/mx .25/us .18/co .12); a non-null `app_version_min` trims via
  `appVersionScale` (deterministic from the version string, always in 0.55–0.90). So narrowing plausibly
  lowers totals, deterministically. `hasFilterConflict` left untouched (distinct intentional mechanic).
- `buildSeries` exported for unit testing.

**Tests** (`src/services/mock/result-engine.test.ts`, 8 new): determinism (same filters → same numbers);
platform / country / app_version_min changes each change the numbers; platform order-independence;
and three "narrowing reduces magnitude" directional checks (single platform / one country / version floor
each total less than unfiltered).

