## 2026-07-16 — Session 7: series labels now respect the active filter

**Bug (found by the user testing the Docker build, same file as Session 6):** `seriesLabels()` chose the
rendered series/legend lines purely from the chart's `group_by` dimension, ignoring `filters` entirely.
So a country-grouped chart always drew Brazil/Mexico/Colombia lines regardless of `filters.country`, and
a platform-grouped chart always drew both iOS and Android. Real-backend equivalent: Pinot applies the
WHERE filter BEFORE grouping, so groups outside the filter never come back — the frontend should never
render series for filtered-out dimension values. (Distinct from Session 6, which fixed the *magnitude/
shape* of each series; this is about *which* series exist.)

Also fixed alongside: the `"country"` label set only listed three countries — `"us"` (United States) was
missing, so filtering a country-grouped chart to the US produced no matching series at all.

**Fix** (`src/services/mock/result-engine.ts`): `seriesLabels(chart, filters)` now narrows the label set:
- `group_by "country"` → single country's label when `filters.country` is set; all **four** (br/mx/co/us,
  fixing the missing US) when unset.
- `group_by "platform"` → only selected platforms (mapped ios→iOS / android→Android), canonical order
  preserved and order-independent; both when the platform filter is empty.
- `group_by "app_version"` → only labels `>= filters.app_version_min` (numeric `compareVersions`); all
  when no floor.
- `default` → unchanged single "Total" line.
`buildSeries` passes `filters` through. `hasFilterConflict` and Session 6's `filterKey`/`filterScale`
untouched (orthogonal concerns).

Concrete example: a country-grouped chart with `country=br` now returns exactly one series — **Brazil** —
instead of all three (now four) countries.

**Tests** (`result-engine.test.ts`, +9): country filter → one matching series; `country=us` → United
States (the previously-missing case); unfiltered country → all four; one platform → one series; no
platform filter → both in canonical order; platform order-independence; `app_version_min` excludes older
labels; no floor → all versions; and default → single Total regardless of filters.

### Verification (2026-07-16, session 7)
- `tsc --noEmit`: PASS · `eslint .`: PASS (0/0) · `next build`: PASS · `npm test`: PASS — **54 tests, 6 files**.
- Docker image rebuilt (`docker compose up -d --build`): container `Up (healthy)`; smoke test on host
  :3100 → `/` 307, `/dashboards` 200, `/charts` 200, `/dashboards/:seededId` 200.

