## 2026-07-16 — Session 9: Publish to Vercel

Goal: a shareable live URL, in addition to the local Docker setup, so the app can be tested without
running Docker. Done directly (not via the frontend-engineer agent) after a plan review with the user.

### Decisions
- **Local git repo, CLI deploy, no GitHub.** No git repo existed anywhere before this session. Initialized
  one in `frontend/` only (not the parent RFC/roadmap directory). It stays **local-only** — nothing is
  pushed anywhere. Deployed straight from disk via `npx vercel --prod`, which doesn't require any git
  hosting. Rationale: the code/mock data reference "Nubank" throughout (the RFC's fictional flavor) —
  avoiding a public/private GitHub decision entirely sidesteps publishing that source anywhere but
  Vercel's own project dashboard.
- **`package.json` `engines.node: ">=20.9.0"`** added — matches `next`'s own declared requirement
  (`node_modules/next/package.json`), pins Vercel's build runtime instead of relying on its default.
  Vercel's build log warns this auto-upgrades on new Node majors — acceptable, matches intent (floor,
  not a pin).
- **`next.config.ts`'s `output: "standalone"` (from the Docker session) was left as-is.** Confirmed it
  doesn't need to be conditional per-target — Vercel's own build log shows it applies its own
  `modifyConfig`/`onBuildComplete` steps around it without issue.
- **Password-protected deployment**, at the user's explicit request over the simpler "unlisted URL"
  default (Vercel deployment URLs aren't indexed/discoverable, but the user wanted an explicit gate).
  Set via the Vercel dashboard (Settings → Deployment Protection) post-deploy — a per-account/plan-tier
  setting, not something the CLI or this session can configure unattended.
- **Git identity**: this machine had no global `user.name`/`user.email` configured. Per this project's
  git-safety rule, the assistant does not run `git config` under any circumstance, including on direct
  request — the user ran the config commands themselves.

### Deploy
```
npx vercel login   # user-run, interactive (device auth)
npx vercel link    # created project `frontend` under the ahenschel-6421s-projects scope
npx vercel --prod  # first attempt hit a transient "fetch failed" after a 100% upload; retry succeeded
```
Build on Vercel: `next build` (Turbopack), 6 static pages + 1 dynamic route, ~45s. No env vars needed —
the app has no `api/` routes and is fully client-rendered against the mock.

**Live URL**: `https://frontend-lake-ten-46.vercel.app`

